        "title": "feat: serve ClawHub docs under /docs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add the ClawHub docs generator/config and wire the app build to serve generated docs at `/docs`.\n- Move the docs auth handoff to `/auth/docs` and proxy `/ask-molty/*` to the docs assistant without forwarding ClawHub credentials.\n- Update ClawHub header navigation so Skills, Plugins, and Docs live in the top navbar, Publishers is removed, nav icons are removed, and theme mode moves into the signed-in profile dropdown.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `bunx vitest run 'server/routes/ask-molty/[...].test.ts' src/lib/docsAuth.test.ts src/routes/auth/-docs.test.tsx src/__tests__/header.test.tsx src/__tests__/ui-design-contract.test.ts src/components/AppProviders.test.tsx convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts convex/publishers.test.ts convex/skills.resolve.test.ts` — 9 files passed, 401 tests passed.\n- `bun run docs:build` — built 17 docs pages and 16 search entries.\n- `bun run docs:smoke` — `clawhub docs smoke ok: 16 search entries`.\n- `VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://example.invalid bun run build` — passed.\n- `bun run ci:static` — passed.\n- `bun run ci:unit` — 259 files passed, 3022 tests passed, coverage above thresholds.\n- `codex review -c model='gpt-5' --uncommitted` — initial run found credential forwarding in the Ask Molty proxy; fixed by stripping Cookie/Authorization and adding regression coverage. Final rerun exited 0 with no findings output.\n\n## Review Notes\n\n- Generated docs output is intentionally ignored under `public/docs/`; production build regenerates it before the app build.\n- Existing in-browser docs/Molty proof was not regenerated for this PR update.\n",
